title: pepsi_japan_cola_challenge_(meme)
body:
A series of promos run by [[Pepsi]] in Japan for its Japan Cola, starring soccer player "Honda Keisuke":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Keisuke_Honda]. In the original promo, running from April 9th to April 19th, 2019, Twitter users who followed Pepsi Japan's Twitter account would reply to "this post":[https://twitter.com/pepsi_jpn/status/1115434153913143296] (or "its":[https://twitter.com/pepsi_jpn/status/1117970868011880448] "reposts":[https://twitter.com/pepsi_jpn/status/1118695643038527488] as the end date approached) by "playing" a virtual version of [[rock paper scissors|rock, paper, scissors]] against Keisuke. After a period of time, an automated response of Honda‚Äôs move was given ("example":[https://twitter.com/pepsi_jpn/status/1118695772315430912]). This format would be similarly used for the second and third runs of this promo, with the "second":[https://twitter.com/pepsi_jpn/status/1148049061674704896] involving a "card battle":[https://twitter.com/pepsi_jpn/status/1151310550720307200] (example of response "given":[https://twitter.com/pepsi_jpn/status/1151431492028882945]), running from July 8th to July 22nd, 2019, and the "third":[https://twitter.com/pepsi_jpn/status/1183925460461182977] involving a coin toss, one side having a K and the other H (example of response "given":[https://twitter.com/pepsi_jpn/status/1183940981013528576]), running from October 15th to October 28th, 2019. A "fourth":[https://twitter.com/pepsi_jpn/status/1260026910643572736] campaign ran from May 12th to May 22nd, 2020, once more having users play a game of rock, paper, scissors against Keisuke. A "fifth":[https://twitter.com/pepsi_jpn/status/1285031673617408004] campaign ran from July 21st to July 27th, where, "based":[https://twitter.com/pepsi_jpn/status/1285046774122651649] on the day, folks challenged Keisuke in one of the three previous games.

Consecutive challenges, such as from June 22 to July 5th, 2021, would not feature Keisuke.

The original promo was a campaign allowing people to win coupons to be exchanged for 600-mL bottles of Japan Cola at [[FamilyMart]] or [[Lawson]], with players attempting to win coupons by replying to the aforementioned post. It was infamous for being extremely difficult and nearly impossible to win in "with a rate of 0.41% as calculated by one user":[https://twitter.com/OK_im_fine_now/status/1117822329579376640], with subsequent promos keeping up the infamy.

h4. External links

title: battle_of_arnhem
body:
[b]The Battle of Arnhem[/b] was a battle of [[World War II]] at the vanguard of the Allied [[Operation Market Garden]]. 

It was fought in and around the Dutch city of [[Arnhem]], the town of Oosterbeek, the villages Wolfheze and Driel and the vicinity from 17 to 26 September 1944 and ended in [[germany|German]] victory. The Allies were poised to enter the Netherlands after sweeping through France and Belgium in the summer of 1944, after the [[Invasion of Normandy]]. 

The 1st Airborne Division landed some distance from its objectives and was hampered by unexpected resistance, especially from elements of the 9th and 10th SS Panzer Divisions. Only a small force was able to reach the [[john_frost_bridge|Arnhem road bridge]] while the advance of the main body of the division was stopped on the outskirts of the town. XXX Corps was unable to advance north from Nijmegen in the [[Battle of Nijmegen]] as quickly as planned and the British airborne troops were not relieved according to schedule. After four days, the small British force at the bridge was overwhelmed and the rest of the division trapped in a small pocket north of the river. The paratroops could not be sufficiently reinforced by the Poles or XXX Corps when they arrived on the southern bank, nor by Royal Air Force supply flights. After nine days of fighting, the remnants of the division were withdrawn in Operation Berlin. The Allies were unable to advance further with no secure bridges over the Nederrijn and the front line stabilised south of Arnhem. The 1st Airborne Division lost nearly three quarters of its strength and did not see combat again.

title: battle_of_the_bulge
body:
[b]The Battle of the Bulge[/b], also known as [b]the Ardennes Offensive[/b], was the last major German offensive campaign on the Western Front during [[World War II]]. 

The battle lasted for five weeks from 16 December 1944 to 28 January 1945, towards the end of the war in Europe. It was launched through the densely forested Ardennes region between Belgium and [[Luxembourg]]. The goal of the German offensive was to seize the harbor at Antwerp, an important Ally source of supplies, equipment and military support, so they could stop the eventual Allied advance into [[Germany]]. In order to reach it before the Allies could regroup and bring their superior air power to bear, German mechanized forces had to seize the roadways through eastern [[Belgium]] as soon as possible.

The Germans achieved a total surprise attack on the morning of 16 December, due to a combination of Allied overconfidence, preoccupation with Allied offensive plans, and poor aerial reconnaissance due to bad weather. American forces bore the brunt of the attack and their fierce resistance on the northern shoulder of the offensive, around Elsenborn Ridge, and in the south, around Bastogne, blocked German access to key roads to the northwest and west that they counted on for success. 

The battle ended with an Allied [[victory]] and a significant [[defeat]] and depletion of the already exhausted German forces in fuel, armor and soldiers. From among the Americans' peak strength of 610,000 troops there were 81,000 battle casualties, including at least 8,400 killed. The "Bulge" was the largest and bloodiest single battle fought by the [[United States]] in World War II and the third-deadliest campaign in American military history.

h4. See also

* [[Siege of Bastogne]]

title: battle_of_remagen
body:
[b]The Battle of Remagen[/b] was an 18-day battle during the Allied invasion of [[Germany]] in the last part of [[World War II]], from 7 to 25 March 1945, when [[united_states|American]] forces unexpectedly captured the Ludendorff Bridge over the Rhine intact. 

The U.S. soldiers were able to succesfully hold it against hard German opposition and build additional temporary crossings. The presence of a bridgehead across the Rhine advanced by three weeks the Western Allies' planned crossing of the Rhine into the German interior and greatly accelerated the fall of The Third Reich and the [[victory]] of Allied forces in Europe.

title: winter_offensive
body:
[b]The winter campaign of 1941‚Äì1942[/b], also known as [b]The Winter Offensive[/b], was the name given by [[Soviet]] [[military]] command to the period  from 5 December 1941 to 7 May 1942 that marked the commencement of the [b]Moscow Strategic Offensive Operation[/b] (better known as [b]the Battle of Moscow[/b]) against [[Nazi]] [[Germany]] in [[World War II]]. 

The Soviet defensive effort frustrated [[Adolf Hitler]]'s attack on [[Moscow]], the capital and largest city of the [[Soviet Union]]. Moscow was one of the primary military and political objectives for the Axis forces in their invasion of the Soviet Union.

The opening phase of the [[soviet_army|Red Army]] strategic counter-offensive operations in the Soviet Union was a major albeit costly Soviet [[victory]].

title: prague_offensive
body:
[b]The Prague offensive[/b] (Russian: –ü—Ä–∞–∂—Å–∫–∞—è —Å—Ç—Ä–∞—Ç–µ–≥–∏—á–µ—Å–∫–∞—è –Ω–∞—Å—Ç—É–ø–∞—Ç–µ–ª—å–Ω–∞—è –æ–ø–µ—Ä–∞—Ü–∏—è, romanized: [i]Prazhskaya strategicheskaya nastupatel'naya operatsiya[/i], lit. 'Prague strategic offensive') was the last major [[military]] operation of [[World War II]] in Europe. 

The offensive was fought on the Eastern Front from 6 May to 11 May 1945. Fought concurrently with the Prague uprising, the offensive significantly helped the liberation of [[Czechoslovakia]] in 1945. The offensive was one of the last engagements of World War II in Europe and continued after [[Nazi]] [[Germany]]'s unconditional capitulation on 8/9 May.

The city of Prague was ultimately liberated by the [[Soviet Union]] during the Prague offensive. All of the German troops of Army Group Centre (Heeresgruppe Mitte) and many of Army Group Ostmark (formerly known as Army Group South) were killed or captured, or fell into the hands of the Allies after the capitulation.

title: battle_of_the_dnieper
body:
[b]The Battle of the Dnieper[/b] was a military campaign that took place in 1943 on the Eastern Front of [[World War II]]. 

Being one of the largest operations of the war, it involved almost four million troops at one point and stretched over a 1,400 kilometres (870 mi) front. Over four months, the eastern bank of the Dnieper was recovered from [[Nazi]] [[germany|German]] forces by five of the [[soviet army|Red Army]]'s fronts, which conducted several assault river crossings to establish several lodgements on the western bank. 

2,438 Red Army soldiers were awarded the title Hero of the Soviet Union for their involvement.

title: kikou_senki_dragonar
body:
[b]Kikou Senki Dragonar[/b], also known as [b]Metal Armor Dragonar[/b], is a 48 episode [[mecha]] anime [[science fiction]] TV series, created by Nippon Sunrise (later renamed [[sunrise_(company)|Sunrise]] during production) that aired from 1987 to 1988. 

Devised shortly after the release of Mobile Suit [[Gundam ZZ]], Dragonar was intended to be both a "starter" series to get new fans into mecha anime, and a potential successor to the Gundam franchise. In fact, its concept and plot are said to be a renewal of [[mobile_suit_gundam|the first Gundam]]; and its mecha were designed by [[Ookawara Kunio]], the mechanical designer for most of the [[Gundam]] series.

Though the series enjoyed good ratings and earned a loyal fan following, it failed to surpass Gundam and ended up as a single series, probably due to its light, ZZ Gundam‚Äìlike take on the real robot mecha genre. [[Video game]] developer "Banpresto":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Banpresto had Dragonar appear in two of its popular franchises, [[Super Robot Wars]] and [[Another Century's Episode]]; fans responded positively, and Sunrise acknowledged them in 2005 by releasing a memorial DVD collection of the series, a remastered version of the previous two-part laserdisc box set released years before.

title: gran_class
body:
The nicest available accommodation on [[Shinkansen]] trains. Gran class seating is found on [[e5 hayabusa|E5]]/[[h5 hayabusa|H5]] trains used on Hayabusa, Hayate, Yamabiko, and Nasuno services on the Tohoku and Hokkaido Shinkansen, and E7/W7 trains used on Kagayaki, Hakutaka, Tsurugi, Asama, Toki, and Tanigawa services on the Joetsu and Hokuriku Shinkansen. Seating is in a 2+1 configuration, with the legroom, seat width, and recline being greater than that of the green car seen on all other [[Shinkansen]] routes. The seats are cream leather with a white headrest, and feature power adjustability, a fold-up leg rest, and a reading light. The gran class cabin has only 18 seats and is located in either the first or last car of the train, that being car 10 of [[e5 hayabusa|E5]]/[[h5 hayabusa|H5]], and car 12 of E7/W7 trains. In addition to luxurious seating, complimentary food and drinks, and hostess services are also included.

h4. External links
* "East Japan Railway Company":[https://www.jreast.co.jp/granclass/en/]

title: center_axis_relock_stance
body:
A gun-wielding stance invented before 2011, later popularized by the [[John Wick]] film series. The stance was designed as an effective shooting system for close-quarters self-defense, while minimizing recoil and the user's target profile. The stance has the gun hold close to the body, the body bladed towards the target, with the shoulders placed almost perpendicular to the target (or parallel to the gun, if that makes more sense), supporting shoulder pointed more forward.

[[John Wick (character)|]], and [[Nishikigi Chisato]] of [i][[Lycoris Recoil]][/i] use it.

title: pikmin_(creature)
body:
The titular plant-like organisms from the [[Pikmin (Series)|]] series. They come in multiple varieties and have three distinct developmental stages (leaf, bud and flower).

h5. Introduced in [[Pikmin 1]]

* [[Red Pikmin]]: The only Pikmin with noses, they are red in color and have immunity to fire.
* [[Yellow Pikmin]]: The only Pikmin with ears, they are yellow in color and are the lightest of the Pikmin. They can use small [[bomb rock]]s and have immunity to electricity. 
* [[Blue Pikmin]]: These Pikmin have mouth-like gills and are the only Pikmin who can survive being underwater. They are blue in color.

h5. Introduced in [[Pikmin 2]]

* [[White Pikmin]]: The smallest of the Pikmin, they are the fastest and have immunity to poison as well as being toxic themselves. They have large red eyes and are white in color, similar to an [[albino]].
* [[Purple Pikmin]]: The only Pikmin with hair, they are the strongest but slowest of the Pikmin with a single Purple Pikmin having the strength of ten non-purple Pikmin. They are the bulkiest of the Pikmin and are purple in color.

title: imi_galil
body:
The [b]IMI Galil[/b] is a [[weapon family|family]] of military [[gun|firearms]] that first entered service in 1972, designed by Yisrael Galili and Yakov Lior in the late 1960s. Recognizable by its [[flip-up sight|flip-up]] aperture sights on the dust cover, vertical charging handle, rectangular one-piece handguard, skeletonized metal [[folding stock]] and a gas block with straighter profile. Based on the [[Rk62]] and similarly utilizing an AK-style gas piston system, it has been developed into several variants, such as: 

* [b]Galil AR[/b] - the original 5.56mm [[assault rifle]] with slightly-curved slimmer rectangular handguard. (post #1293721)
* [b]Galil ARM[/b] - [[light machine gun]] with notably blockier wooden handguard, carry handle and a "wire-cutter" [[bipod]]. (post #1333214)
* [b]Galil SAR "Glilon"[/b] - shorter variant of Galil AR. Smallest one is the Galil MAR. (post #1985402)
* [b]Galil 7.62[/b] - [[battle rifle]] chambered in 7.62√ó51mm NATO. Notice the thicker, straight box magazine. Unlike curved ones belong to the three 5.56mm counterparts. (post #6409080)
* [b][[IMI Galil Galatz|Galil Galatz]][/b] - distinctively equipped with a scope and bipod for sniper/designated marksman use. Has (post #6003226)
* This tag can also apply to the South African-produced [b]Vektor R4[/b]. (post #3181449)

h4. See also

title: fn_fal
body:
The [b]FAL[/b] ([i]Fusil Automatique L√©ger[/i], "Light Automatic Rifle") is a Belgian-designed 7.62√ó51mm NATO [b][[battle rifle]][/b]. It was developed between 1947-1953 by "Dieudonn√© Saive":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dieudonn√©_Saive] at [[FN Herstal]]. Known as "the right arm of the Free World", it was the second most widely used [[military]] [[rifle]] in the world (after the AK) during the [[Cold War]], being used by 77 different nations. was nearly adopted by the United States Army as well, but was rejected in favor of the M14.

Identifying characteristics include the tubular charging handle on the left side on the receiver, the shape and location of the [[muzzle device]] and front sight post, and barrel length exposed before the perforated triangular handguard (useful for differentiating it from Heckler & Koch [[weapon]]s of similar profile, such as the [[H&K G3|G3]]). This tag applies to any full-length FAL variants, such as the British L1A1, Austrian StG58, and the Israeli IMI Romat with tubular handguard.

[b]Horikoshi Jirou[/b] (22 June 1903 ‚Äì 11 January 1982) was the main designer of several Japanese war planes, among them the Mitsubishi [[A5M]] and its successor, the legendary Mitsubishi [[A6M Zero]]; both aircraft were used by the Empire of [[Japan]] during [[World War II]].

This tag is applied to all about "Cthulhu Mythos" by [[H P Lovecraft]] and his works.

Lovecraft's guiding aesthetic and philosophical principle was what he termed "cosmicism" or "cosmic horror", the idea that life is incomprehensible to human minds and that the universe is fundamentally inimical to the interests of humankind. The R32 was the third Skyline to have a [[Nissan Skyline GT-R|GT-R]] variant, reviving the badge 16 years after the [[Nissan skyline c110|C110]] GT-R's discontinuation. Designed for Group A racing in particular, the GT-R version debuted shortly after the base model and was sold for another year after the base R32 had been phased out.

This generation of the Skyline is notable for several appearances in racing anime and games. Several R32s were featured in [[Initial D]], where they are driven by [[Nakazato Takeshi]], Shimamura Eikichi, and Houjou Rin. In [[Wangan Midnight]] R32s are driven by [[Akikawa Reina]], Hiramoto Kouichi, and Tomoya.

title: h_p_lovecraft
body:
[b]Howard Phillips Lovecraft[/b] (August 20, 1890 ‚Äì March 15, 1937) ‚Äî known as [b]H. P. Lovecraft[/b] ‚Äî was an American author of horror, fantasy and [[science fiction]], especially the subgenre known as weird fiction.

Lovecraft's guiding aesthetic and philosophical principle was what he termed "cosmicism" or "cosmic horror", the idea that life is incomprehensible to human minds and that the universe is fundamentally inimical to the interests of humankind. As such, his stories express a profound indifference to human beliefs and affairs. He is best known for his [[Cthulhu Mythos]] story cycle and the [[Necronomicon]], a fictional grimoire of magical rites and forbidden lore.

Although Lovecraft's readership was limited during his lifetime, his reputation has grown over the decades, and he is now regarded as one of the most influential horror writers of the 20th century. His stories have also been adapted into many plays, films and games.

title: nissan_skyline_c110
body:
The fourth generation of the [[Nissan Skyline]], produced from 1972-1977. Notable for it's [[muscle car]]-styled design, inspired by popular American cars of the time.

Like it's [[nissan skyline c10|predecessor]], the C110 had a [[nissan Skyline GT-R|GT-R]] performance variant. Launched in September 1972, this generation's GT-R version was only produced for 7 months before being discontinued as the impact of the 1973 oil crisis caused sports cars to fall out of favor in Japan. A total of 197 C110 GT-Rs were produced during it's short run, and the GT-R badge as a whole was discontinued until the [[nissan skyline r32|R32]]'s GT-R variant launched 16 years later.

title: muscle_car
body:
A high performance and potent [[car]], usually American, sometimes Australian, British or South African. Distinctive characteristics include a large, heavy frame similar to a mid-size family sedan, a huge V8 engine with at least 4 liters (244 CID) of displacement, a gearbox with extremely tight ratios, an interior with enough room for 4 people, and a price that is much lower than an European simile. Due to their poor handling and their fabulous acceleration, they are best suited for straight-line drag racing.

Examples of muscle cars include the AMC Machine, the [[Chevrolet Chevelle]], the Ford Torino, and the 2010 [[Dodge Challenger]].

Similar in concept is the pony car, which is basically a smaller, lighter muscle car, such as the [[Ford Mustang]], the 1970 [[Dodge Challenger]], or the [[Chevrolet Camaro]]. While not often considered muscle cars, many Japanese cars in the 70s (such as the [[Nissan Skyline C110]], [[Toyota Celica A20]], and [[Mitsubishi Galant GTO]]) featured styling that made them resemble compact muscle cars.

title: incan
body:
The [b]Inca Empire[/b], or [b]Inka Empire[/b] (Quechua: [i]Tawantinsuyu[/i]), was the largest empire in the pre-Columbian American Continent. 

The administrative, political and military center of the empire was located in Cusco in modern-day [[Peru]]. 

The Inca civilization arose from the highlands of Peru sometime in the early 13th century. 

From 1438 to 1533, the Incas used a variety of methods, from conquest to peaceful assimilation, to incorporate a large portion of western South America, centered on the Andean mountain ranges, including large parts of modern Ecuador, Peru, western and south central Bolivia, northwest Argentina, north and north-central Chile, and southern Colombia into a state comparable to the historical empires of the Old World.

The empire ended in 1533 with the arrival of the European [[spain|Spaniards]], who conquered it.

Participated in several American motorsport series during it's production, including [[NASCAR]] and Trans Am.

The model was ultimately discontinued in 2023, as part of [[Dodge (company)|]] (and the Stellantis Group as a whole) moving towards a fully electric lineup. No direct successor to the Challenger was announced at the time of it's discontinuation, instead the [[Dodge Charger]] received a new, muscle car-styled electric coupe to replace the long-standing sedan.

It is said to be a [[Tankdramon]] that sustained critical damage during an operation to capture a [[BanchoLeomon|CODENAME: BAN-TYO]] was brought back to the D-Brigade's headquarters and powered up by injecting the mysterious Dark Matter substance into it - however, the operation backfired when an excessive amount of it was added, causing the freshly evolved creature to destroy the building and run away, carrying the mighty Gigastick Lance in its right arm. It allegedly has a one-track mind, and is rumored to still be hunting "CODENAME: BAN-TYO"...

title: chaosmon
body:
An Ultimate [[Digimon (creature)|]] that is the result of the Jogress between [[Darkdramon]] and [[BanchoLeomon]]. As it failed to properly Jogress, its two Digicores lie exposed on its shoulders, and it is an extremely unstable Digimon destined to be erased from existence. According to the Central Dogma of the Digital World, 'Chaosmon' is the codename for Digimon that 'should not exist'. Its left arm, the Darkdra Arm, is equipped with the Gigastick Cannon (explaining the Arm Cannon tag), while its Banchou Arm is equipped with the BAN-TYO Blade. The Digimoji on the Blade say 'KAOSU', transcribed as 'CHAOS', which hints at its name.

Another variant exists, called Chaosmon: Valdur Arm, which is the Jogress between [[Valdurmon]] and [[BanchoLeomon]]. There is also [[UltimateChaosmon]], a Jogress between all of [[Darkdramon]], [[BanchoLeomon]], [[Valdurmon]] and [[Sleipmon]].

[[Chaosmon]] and the [[Digimon]] related to it debuted in the Digimon Accel V-Pets in 2005.

title: titan_(submersible)
body:
An experimental tourism [[submarine|submersible]] built by OceanGate, designed to take rich customers to the [[shipwreck|wreckage]] of the [[rms titanic|Titanic]]. It used a cylindrical design with a carbon fiber body, had a capacity of five people, even an onboard [[toilet|lavatory]], and was controlled by a [[Logitech]] F710 [[game controller|gaming controller.]] Its design was heavily criticized by submarine experts and was largely made of off-the-shelf components (such as using construction pipes for ballast).

On [[2023 titan submersible incident|June 18, 2023]], 740 kilometers off the coast of Newfoundland, [[Canada]], its surface ship lost contact with the Titan 1 hour & 45 minutes into the dive, but didn't call for help until 8 hours later, after the sub was supposed to return. Multiple government agencies from the [[United States]] and [[Canada]] were involved in the massive search spanning four days and  over 25000 square kilometers. By June 22, the date when the emergency oxygen was predicted to be depleted, an ROV had located debris which was confirmed to be part of the sub, and later had been determined that the vessel had imploded. All 5 people onboard, including OceanGate's CEO have been declared dead. Subsequent investigations revealed the vessel was practically doomed from the start, due to poor design and ignorance by the company's CEO, including him firing an expert for telling him his vessel was not seaworthy and previously saying things that essentially amounted to "screw safety."

title: avenger_(dungeon_and_fighter)
body:
[[dungeon_and_fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character. Subclass of the [[male priest (dungeon and fighter)|male Priest]]. Also known as the Doom Guardian or Immortal.

His "default appearance":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/6/65/AvengerPortrait.png] puts him in a black hooded jacket with skull pauldrons, red dress vest, and black pants. His signature weapon, the scythe, is seen hanging on his back.

As a "Doom Guardian":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/3/39/Immortal.png], his outfit is mostly the same, save for a black shirt under his jacket. His arm is seen undergoing a demonic transformation, turning it ash black, with his eyes glowing yellow.

As a "Neo Avenger":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/8/80/Neo-_Avenger_Artwork.png], his outfit is mostly the same as his Doom Guardian outfit. He's shown further along his demonic transformation,  which is now taking up the entire right side of his body; his torn shirt shows glowing yellow symbols where his skin has transformed.

title: monk_(dungeon_and_fighter)
body:
[[dungeon_and_fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character. Subclass of the [[male priest (dungeon and fighter)|male Priest]]. Also known as the Templar or Justice.

His "default appearance":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/c/cf/MonkPortrait.png] features longer, waist-length hair tied into a ponytail, with his outfit consisting of a black tanktop with a white cross printed on it and a pair of maroon pants with black stripes. He wields white metal knuckles with gold cross-shaped studs on them.

As a "Justice":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/0/03/Justice.png], his hair is cut short, more resembling his base class, and has gray streaks running through it. His top is now a black shirt with a gold outline of a cross and wears gray pants, with a white jacket hanging off of his shoulders.

As a "Neo Monk":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/d/d2/Neo-_Monk_Artwork.png], his outfit is a combination of his Justice hairstyle and Monk clothes. He wields an oversized, flat-faced gauntlet in his right hand.

title: exorcist_(dungeon_and_fighter)
body:
[[dungeon_and_fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character. Subclass of the [[male priest (dungeon and fighter)|male Priest]]. Also known as the Hyperion or Draconid.

His "default appearance":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/b/bd/ExorcistPortrait.png] has longer brown hair, wearing Eastern-themed red and white robes. A set of Buddhist prayer beads is wrapped across his torso and right wrist, and a white rope sash with a gourd hanging off of it is tied to his waist.

As a "Draconid":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/c/c1/Exo2nd.png], his hair is shorter, but still long enough to tie into a small ponytail. His outfit is more traditionally Chinese, with a sleeveless black top with Eastern dragon imagery. A long, white cloth with black trim hangs around his waist. He is seen using both his prayer beads and a large, golden battle axe as weapons.

As a "Neo Exorcist":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/0/04/Neo-_Exorcist_Artwork.png], his hair is worn loose and ragged, with his beard graying. He's now seen topless, exposing a black Eastern dragon tattoo along his left arm and shoulder. The only clothes he wears are a pair of black pants, a brown and yellow sash, and wrappings around his ankles.

title: leomon
body:
Leomon is a [[muscular]] lion-man with orange fur, yellow mane, yellow fur on its legs and the tip of its tail, [[blue eyes]], black nose and mouth, five fingers on its hands and feet, black claws, black ear tips, and scars on its arms, left foot, and the left side of its face. Its ears are on top of its head. 

It wears a golden earring on its left ear, a [[collar]] with with a blue [[gem]] in the middle and multiple red teeth around it, [[black pants]] with yellow cords forming multiple "X" on its side, a black belt with a square metallic buckle on its waist, three others on its left arm, another in its left hand, and another in the pantleg. It carries its [[sword]] in the back on its belt.

It is called the "King of Beasts", as well as the "Noble Hero". While most [[Digimon]] are ferocious, it possesses a strong will and a heart of justice, and has defeated a great number of fiendish [[Digimon]]. Also, it is a rival to the "Digimon Hunter" [[Orgemon]], who runs the whole gamut of destruction. Its tough flesh, tempered well by daily training, can endure any attack, and since it chokes the life out of the opponent with its quick attacks, 

Leomon can be said to be an outstanding Combat Species. It carries a sentient magical [[sword]] called "Beast Sword" (ÁçÖÂ≠êÁéã‰∏∏ Shishiou-maru?, lit. "Lion King") on its waist. Also, it is matchless friends with [[Garudamon]], who possesses the same will. [[Cyclonemon]]'s right eye was crushed by Leomon.

The original Steyr HS-50 was designed by Heinrich Fortmeier, on behalf of Steyr Arms. Unlicensed variants of the HS. 50 include the AM-50 Sayyad produced by Iran and the Golan S-01 produced by Syria. The HS .460 variant is chambered in .460 Steyr [[ammunition|cartridge]] instead.

title: gensou_suikoden_iv
body:
The fourth game in the [i][[Gensou Suikoden]][/i] series. It is the first prequel game of the series, taking place 150 years before [i][[Gensou Suikoden I]][/i]. It takes place among the Island Nations, to the south of [i]Gensou Suikoden I[/i]'s Scarlet Moon Empire, during an invasion by the Kooluk Empire which was engineered by "Merchant of Death" Graham Cray, and follows exiled Gaien Knight [[Lazlo (suikoden)|]]. Lazlo, following the usual [i]Gensou Suikoden[/i] formula, becomes the host of a True Rune (the cursed Rune of Punishment) and the leader of the rebel military. Due to its location, travel and major battles in the game are carried out by ship instead of on land. It also has the fewest returning characters of any game in the series, with four characters from previous games who were already established as immortal being present.

Due to its simplified gameplay (especially the reduction of party size from the traditional six to only four), annoyingly frequent random battles, and a story that never really lives up to its potential, [i]Gensou Suikoden IV[/i] is widely considered the worst in the series.

title: gensou_suikoden_iii
body: The third game in the [i][[Gensou Suikoden]][/i] series. It takes place 18 years after the first game, and is set just west of [i][[Gensou Suikoden II]][/i]'s Dunan region. The game revolves around a war between the Grassland tribes and the Zexen Confederacy, with later interference by Holy Kingdom of Harmonia, the sole superpower in the [i]Gensou Suikoden[/i] world. [i]Gensou Suikoden III[/i] is unique in the series in that it follows three different main characters: [[hugo (suikoden iii)|Hugo]] (son of one of the Grassland tribal chiefs), [[Chris Lightfellow]] (Captain of the Zexen Knights), and [[Geddoe (suikoden)|]] (a mercenary initially working for Harmonia). body:
[[Mecha]] featured in the 1980s anime TV show [[Kikou Souseiki Mospeada]].

It has 3 modes: Armo-Fighter ([[Jet]]/[[Starfighter]]), Armo-Soldier ([[Giant]] [[Robot]]) and Armo-Diver ([[Gerwalk]]). The Legioss can be connected in tandem with the [[Tread]] heavy mecha (which acts as an aerospace booster).

In [[real life]] this mecha was designed by [[Aramaki Shinji]] in the early 80s.

The Legioss is somewhat similar in design to the [[VF-1]] [b]Valkyrie[/b] variable fighter from [[Choujikuu Yousai Macross]] (1982), which aired a year before [[Mospeada]] (1983).

title: bell_jar
body:
A [i]bell jar[/i], also known as a [i]cloche[/i] or [i]display dome[/i], is a bell-shaped vessel made usually of glass and sometimes of plastic and designed to cover objects or contain gases or a vacuum.  These objects have various purposes.  In a household setting, they were normally used as a protective dust cover for the object covered by it.  In a lab setting, they were used to trap gasses or vacuums within the container, in this setting they're specifically referred to as a [i]bell jar[/i].  In an agricultural setting, they were used to cover outdoor plants to protect them from frost, in this setting they're specifically referred to as a [i]cloche[/i].

A bell jar may or may not have a knob at the top to serve as a handle when picking it up.

title: camel_clutch
body:
A [[wrestling]] move where the wrestler sits on the back of his opponent, who is face down on the mat, and places the arm or, more commonly, both arms of the opponent on his thighs. The wrestler then reaches around the opponent's head and applies a chinlock and then leans back and pulls the opponent's head and torso.

A camel clutch can also refer simply to a rear chinlock while seated on the back of an opponent, without placing the arms on the thighs. The move was invented by Gory Guerrero in Mexico, where it was called la de a caballo (Horse-mounting choke), but got its more common name from Ed Farhat, who wrestled as "The Sheik" and used it as his finisher. The late [[WWE]] Hall of Famer The Iron Sheik also used it as well. 

A standing variation of the camel clutch is also used, with this variation popularized by Scott Steiner in the late 1990s as he used it as his finisher dubbed the "Steiner Recliner". Steiner's nephew, WWE wrestler Bron Breakker, also uses the Recliner as one of his finishing moves.  

Current [[All Elite Wrestling]] wrestler Miro also uses the camel clutch (which he formerly named as "The Accolade" during his past WWE run as Rusev) which he currently calls as the "Game Over".

title: platoon
body:
[i]The first casualty of war is innocence...-[/i] Main tagline.

[i][b]Platoon[/b][/i] is a 1986 American anti-war film written and directed by Oliver Stone, starring an ensemble of several actors lead by Tom Berenger, [[Willem Dafoe]], and [[Charlie Sheen]]. 

It is the first film of a trilogy of Vietnam War films directed by Stone, followed by [i][b]Born on the Fourth of July[/b][/i] (1989) and [i][b]Heaven & Earth[/b][/i] (1993).

Stone wrote the screenplay based upon his own brutal, terrible and traumatic personal experiences as a [[united states|U.S.]] [[soldier|infantryman]] in the [[Vietnam War]], to counter the falsely heroic and pro-militaristic vision of the war portrayed in John Wayne's [i][b]The Green Berets[/b][/i] (1968). 

Platoon was the first Hollywood film to be written and directed by an actual veteran of the Vietnam War.

Platoon won the Academy Award for Best Picture of 1986; it also won Best Director for Oliver Stone, as well as Best Sound Mixing and Best Film Editing. In 1998, the American Film Institute placed Platoon at #83 in their "AFI's 100 Years... 100 Movies" poll.

title: sope_(food)
body:
A [b]sope[/b] ([[spanish_text|Spanish]] pronunciation: [Ààso.pe]) is a traditional [[mexico|Mexican]] dish consisting of a fried masa base with savory toppings. Also known as [b]picadita[/b] (in Tierra Caliente, Guerrero), it originates in the central and southern parts of [[Mexico]], where it was sometimes first known as [b]pellizcadas[/b]. It is an [[antojito]] or Mexican fast food, which at first sight looks like an unusually thick [[tortilla]] with vegetables and meat toppings.

The masa base is fried with pinched sides and topped with refried [[beans]], crumbled cheese, [[lettuce]], [[onions]], red or green [[sauce]] and [[sour cream]]. Sometimes other ingredients (mostly different types of [[meat]]s) are also added to create different tastes and styles.

[b]Metal Slug 6[/b] is a run and gun [[video game]] for the Sammy Atomiswave [[arcade]] platform in the [[Metal Slug]] series. It was released in 2006.

A [[PlayStation 2]] port was released on September 14, 2006. A downloadable version was made available on the PlayStation Store for the [[PlayStation 3]] on May 20, 2015. It is also featured in Metal Slug Anthology for the [[Wii]], the PlayStation 2 and the [[PlayStation Portable]]. In 2020, a homebrew conversion was released for the [[SEGA Dreamcast]].

title: battle_of_caen
body:
[b]The Battle for Caen[/b] (June to August 1944) is the name given to fighting between the [[united_kingdom|British]] Second Army and the [[germany|German]] Panzergruppe West in [[World War II]] for control of the city of Caen and its vicinity during the larger [[invasion_of_normandy|Battle of Normandy]] in occupied [[France]]. 

The battles followed [b]Operation Neptune[/b], the Allied landings on the French coast on 6 June 1944 ([[D-Day]]) and ended with a decisive and costly Allied [[victory]]. However, the city of Caen ended up completely destroyed with several French civilian casualties as a consequence.

title: sherman_firefly
body:
The [b]Sherman Firefly[/b] was a [[tank]] used by the [[United Kingdom]] in [[World War II]] that traded mobility for fire power. 

It was based on the ubiquitous US [[M4 Sherman]] tank, but fitted with the powerful 3-inch (76.2 mm) caliber British 17-pounder anti-tank gun as its main weapon to counter the heavy armor used by Germany's [[Wehrmacht]] in the European theater. 

Originally conceived as a stopgap until future more powerful British tank designs came into service, the Sherman Firefly became the most common vehicle mounting the 17-pounder in the war. While the weapon proved effective against the heavier [[germany|German]] tanks, it was difficult to use due to the excess of fumes produced by firing the gun in the cramped turret of the vehicle, which greatly impaired visibility during battle.

title: qrow_branwen
body:
Qrow Branwen is a supporting character in [[RWBY]], a 3DCG series produced by Rooster Teeth.

Qrow is [[Raven Branwen]]'s brother and uncle of [[Ruby Rose]] and [[Yang Xiao Long]]. He is an experienced Huntsman and an ally of the main characters. He has a gloomy, pessimistic personality and a drinking problem.

h4. Abilities

Qrow is a highly experienced and skilled fighter. He wields Harbinger, a large sword that can transform into a scythe and incorporates a built-in shotgun. His semblance (special ability) causes bad luck to others around him. [spoiler]He is also capable of transforming into a crow.[/spoiler]

h4. Physical characteristics

Qrow is a 6'1" tall man with a gangly build and narrow, angular face. He has unkempt graying [[black hair]], narrow [[red eyes]], and sparse [[facial hair|stubble]] along his jaw. He tends to stand with a slight slouch. His voice is raspy.

h4. Attire

Qrow wears a white and grey shirt with black cuffs and lapels, black pants, black dress shoes and a tattered red [[cape]]. He wears a crooked [[cross necklace]] around his neck, a black band around his right wrist and [[ring]]s on several fingers.

h4. External links

https://rwby.fandom.com/wiki/Qrow_Branwen

Wamdus's humanoid form appears as a small [[Harvin]] with a large umbrella, and like [[Galleon_(Granblue_Fantasy)|Galleon]], she seems to share certain characteristics of other races, such as her furry ears similar to those of the erune.
